# Auth & permissions

Better Auth (`src/lib/auth.ts`) handles sign-in. Roles are `admin | power_user | sales | accounting | field_supervisor | field_tech` (`src/config/permissions.ts`).

**Capability-first gating:** effective permissions come from the DB matrix (`RoleCapability`) plus optional `UserCapabilityOverride` (DENY wins). Catalog of ids lives in `src/config/capabilities.ts` and is seeded via `seedCapabilities`. Admin edits the matrix at `/settings/permissions` and per-user overrides at `/settings/users`.

- `requireUser()` loads the user and resolves `capabilities: Set<string>`.
- `requireArea(area)` checks `{area}.access` (settings area = either permissions or users manage).
- `requireCapability(id)` / `assertCapability` for fine-grained Server Action gates.
- Do **not** hardcode `user.role === "admin"` for authorization — use capabilities (`materials.force_delete`, etc.).
- Client nav filters by capabilities (`src/config/nav.ts`); that is UX only — every Server Action must re-check.

`src/proxy.ts` only checks for a session cookie. Don't move permission logic into `proxy.ts`.

Desktop-only pages call `requireDesktopSurface(pathname)`. Settings and materials are desktop-only (`src/lib/device-surface.ts`).
